## Perspectives

The rise of the Thalmor raises a fundamental question about Tamrielic politics: was the Oblivion Crisis simply exploited by the Thalmor, or was it deliberately provoked? Some theorists suggest that the Thalmor, with its deep knowledge of metaphysics, may have anticipated — or even facilitated — the end of the Septim dynasty.

What is undeniable is that every major event of the Fourth Era flows, directly or indirectly, from this seizure of power. The Thalmor is not merely an actor in history — it has become its primary engine, shaping the fate of an entire continent according to its ideological vision.
